{"title":"Snowdrops","author":{"name":"Louise Glück"},"publishDate":"2012-12-28","lines":[{"line":"Do you know what I was, how I lived? You know","stanza":1,"number":1},{"line":"what despair is; then","stanza":1,"number":2},{"line":"winter should have meaning for you.","stanza":1,"number":3},{"line":"I did not expect to survive,","stanza":2,"number":4},{"line":"earth suppressing me. I didn’t expect","stanza":2,"number":5},{"line":"to waken again, to feel","stanza":2,"number":6},{"line":"in damp earth my body","stanza":2,"number":7},{"line":"able to respond again, remembering","stanza":2,"number":8},{"line":"after so long how to open again","stanza":2,"number":9},{"line":"in the cold light","stanza":2,"number":10},{"line":"of earliest spring—","stanza":2,"number":11},{"line":"afraid, yes, but among you again","stanza":3,"number":12},{"line":"crying yes risk joy","stanza":3,"number":13},{"line":"in the raw wind of the new world.","stanza":4,"number":14}]}